product.model: Sun Chips Garden Salsa Multigrain Snacks 205g
product.shortDescription: When it comes to zesty, nothing beats the taste of ripe tomatoes and jalapeño peppers delivered right to your mouth on waves of whole grain goodness! SunChips multigrain snacks are a different kind of chip, and when you look closely, you can see that it’s what’s inside those unique waves that make SunChips one-of-a-kind. Every batch is made with 100% whole grains and flavours inspired by fresh tasting ingredients. No artificial flavours, colours or preservatives!With 38 grams of whole grains per 50 g serving, SunChips Garden Salsa flavour multigrain snacks are a nutritious option for when hunger strikes. With flavours inspired by fresh tasting ingredients, add some to your lunch or enjoy them alongside your favourite movie. Bon appétit!

customerReviews.reviewText: Omg sunchips are a must in every house. U don't feel gross eating them but it's such a chip like snack - they are a way healthier alternative and taste so good. Trust me on this you need to get a bag. Even scooping chickpea salad with these chips is amazing.

Tasty, and a bit healthier compared to chips, but since it's a snack it's only healthy in moderation obviously.  The Garden Salsa Sun chips is a nice tangy alternative to the french onion version.  Both flavors are dry as you could expect from multigrain cracker "chips", so it's good to pair with a drink.

I forgot to review my substitutes. Glad that I didn't and that I decided to try these. They're so good. At the whole bag in one day. This and the original flavors are 2 that I never thought of buying. Never thought of these bc I don't like salsa. They don't taste like salsa. I get more of a ranch or nacho cheese doritos vibe. They're also made by the same company as doritos, so I think that's why they taste similar. The nutritional content is a major plus. These are healthier than other chips...yet they taste better.

I've had these in the past and decided my cravings for them was to much for me to withhold myself. The flavors they have to choice from are amazing and give a good texture to any party. Try some dipping sauce of guacamole with it. Spicy of course, you won't be disappointed.
customerReviews.reviewTitle: Makes for a great party and lunch side option.

customerReviews.reviewText: I remember trying Sun Chips when they first come out.  It's been so long ago but I don't think I remember being impressed.  The other day I decided I wanted some chips and I ordered these with the Garden Salsa flavor.  They taste really yummy.  They have a lot of taste without being too overwhelming.  I will be buying more and will probably try some different flavors also.

I can't compare it to the other flavors of SunChips but I can say these have great flavor and I prefer them over most chips! They don't pair well with everything - sometimes you still want a tortilla or potato chip - but these do really well with more simplistic foods that could use some flavor on the side.

OMG I love these chips. Not overseasoned, light crisp chips to feed a snack attack without breaking a tooth or giving a person gastritis. It's gotta be Sun Chip's and it's gotta be Salsa flavored. Oh, and don't let the title Salsa fool you. They are just flavorful enough to give them a light kiss of wonderful flavor without insulting your system indigestion and a burning mouth.

clientResponses.response: Thanks for being a fan AuntBee!!!!

customerReviews.reviewText: I love these chips.   I just hate the price I have to pay for them.  Hoping Walmart makes their version of them so I can get better prices.  I buy occasionally to treat myself, but I would buy all the time if priced reasonably.
These are my favorite chips!! The taste and crunch are perfect. The price and bag size are now prohibited for me though - at $3.46 for a seven ounce bag I am no longer purchasing these.

Having just tried three of the flavours of SunChips after a long break from buying any I can say that they were all a let down in taste. I'd need to use a good quality creamy dip to fight the dryness. That makes it hard to justify paying these prices for a crunchy snack. If I need to make a dip for it then I might as well stick to generic rippled potato chips at the lowest price I can find. SunChips used to be a favourite fancy snack indulgence of mine. Now they all taste like dry cardboard dusted in artificial powders for flavour.

topNegativeReview.reviewText: I was blown away when I looked at the price I paid for these chips. I was hurrying to place my order before time was up. 14.50 for a 7 oz bag of chips is ridiculous.  My mistake to pay that but how many orhers have been taken advantage of.
